node.text: When it comes to gifting, it often can feel really contrived and impersonal. So I'm sharing one of my fave gift ideas that says "hey, I listened, I heard you, and I care " (and it's still pretty and cute and gift-able!). Stay tuned for a fun announcement too! @sajewellness #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Sarah Nicole Landry on August 12, 2021 tagging @sleepcountrycan. May be an image of 2 people, child and indoor.

node.text:
☁️G I V E A W A Y☁️

He’s waited years for this! Finally, Bo is getting his own fresh set up from mattress, pillow, protectors and bedding + a room makeover to suit his tween needs before school is back in session! 

At this age, sleep is a bigger battle than with a newborn, I swear! Sleep is so important to set our kids up for success and optimal sleep is something I know starts with a restful space. 

His last couple mattresses were over a decade old hand-me-downs, which worked as long as they could and Bo never complained! But when I told him a new mattress was on the way AND bedding - I could not have anticipated how overjoyed he would be. 

And well, we’re hoping we can throw that kind of joy back out into the world. 

With the help from my friends @sleepcountrycan we’re giving away to one lucky person/family a $5000 gift card to upgrade your sleep, spend on anything you may need from mattresses, sleep accessories & more.

💤To enter💤
🛌Follow @sleepcountrycan and myself @thebirdspapaya
🛌Comment with what YOU’d like to use that $5000 on! (A king size bed? Crib mattress? Bedding? Dog bed? ALL OF THE THINGS?) 
🛌Tag friends (each comment is an entry!) 

This give away is open exclusively to residents of Canada (excluding Quebec). Must be 18+ to enter. Give away will be closed at 8 PM EST on August 18, 2021. Winners will be announced on August 19, 2021 via comment and direct tag on this Instagram post. Thank you to our #partner @sleepcountrycan. This promotion is in no way sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with, Instagram. 

@sleepcountrycan #sponsored #SleepWellStayWell

node.text:
Don’t let people who have never lived a day in your body tell you that the results of YOUR life / growth / change aren’t valid or normal. They are. Even if it’s different from someone else’s valid and normal experience for themselves and their life. 

Also who said we wanted to be normal? Sounds boring. ✌️

node.text:
How it started, with my baby pooping on me while latching and being stitched the same time 👉 how it’s going. 

Hi. I’m Sarah. 4x mom. Formula feeder. Breastfeeder. Constant don’t-know-what-I’m-doing-er. 

When my first was born I found breastfeeding incredibly uncomfortable and I’m not just talking about the cracked nips. I was so uncomfortable sharing my body that way. I was 21. I was barely over the awkwardness of puberty. 
Then my mental health took a dive. I had no idea what it all meant. I just remember the doctor prescribing me a medication for it and told me I’d have to stop breastfeeding. I remembered seeing in the doctors office a chart showing how expensive formula was compared to free breast milk. I didn’t see how I could afford it. So I just threw out the prescription. Struggled and breastfed. 

Then my second came. I felt a bit better this time. I knew what I was doing. These cool new “hooter hiders” came out and I felt a bit more acceptable feeding. But my baby wasn’t doing well, she cried a lot. We were moving 6 hours away from family, I was not ok. I had to stop and swap to formula. The relief I felt. Oh friends, the relief. It was everything. That baby, well she is a healthy, athletic teenager today. Just needed you to know that. 

Then my boy. The easiest and fastest eater. No issues. And convenience was everything. So we fed no problem. 

Then a decade later. I go back into the ring. I’m excited for it this time. I feel like it’s going to be an enjoyable experience because I no longer feel awkward about it. But I’ve never had a baby that fed as much as this one. “Touched out” was my new way of life. In the early days I cried a lot. Hormones, overwhelmedness. Not loving breastfeeding, not hating it either. Some days I give formula, it helps me manage and have support. Most days I love the convenience of breastfeeding and well, my baby is obsessed. So it’s pretty cute too. 

While this caption is kind of choppy in storytelling, it’s reminiscent of my entire feeding journey. Which is, emotionally and physically all over the place. 

So to cap #worldbreastfeedingweek, I just wanna say… Chest/breast or bottle, baby fed & mama supported, is best🤍

node.text:
There comes a point in your life where your heart tells a bigger story than your body ever could. 

You know the difference between what looks like it is good and well and what actually is. You understand that a body is destined for change. You see yourself as you ebb and flow through seasons of life. 

And you stand in your present, fully knowing that this is a struggle. 
This is a war. 

But the fight feels less about you vs your body and more about you WITH your body taking on life together. 

Assumptions will be made. 
People will talk. 
Stories will be written with your name. 

And so you will hold your head high. 

Because your body is not the story. 
It never was. 
It was merely the cover. 

The story was, and always has been: you.

So you take a deep breath. 
And move through another day. 
Your heart carrying what only the heart knows. 
And your body follows along, ready to support you the best ways it can and knows how. 

I have changed. 
A million times over. 
And a million more times to come. 

But I am not the stillness of a moment. A year. A chapter or two. 
I am an entire story. 
Held within a cover. 

Moving though life. 

Change is not failure. 
Change is an inevitable flow of existence. 
Quite different for each story. 

Post inspired by @busybee.carys I hope you go and read hers too 💖

#ad I told my husband I was taking up golf. I just didn’t specify what *kind* of golf. I do look cute in a golf skirt tho, so maybe you’ll see me on the green soon!

Mario Golf: Super Rush really has brought the whole family (online and at home) together! It’s hard to find something we ALL love sometimes and this sure has been a hit all around. We even brought it on a mini road trip for the kids to play in the backseat as we drove!

Almost 4 years with the SAME Nintendo Switch I bought as a family gift, still going strong with daily use for my own quiet time and wild family game nights.

What have you all been playing? #nintendoswitch

node.text:
⁣They don’t write about this kind of intimacy in romance novels. But I will. 

The first time I laid on my side and Shane reached around to hold me and touched my stomach, we both flinched. This was a rule that now had accidentally been broken. So now what? ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Because I was mortified. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For years I had been hiding and curating my body to be strategically as attractive as it could be because the narrative in my mind told me my body was for others. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
This moment I felt, ruined it all. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
He reacted apologetically as he moved his hand away from my stomach. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Acting in pure emotion, frustration and impulse, I placed my hand on top of his and brought it back to my core. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
Our hands stayed there as he held me. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
I allowed him to wrap his arms around me as silent tears streamed onto my pillow. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Not tears of pain or mortification. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Tears of comfort. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Tears of safety. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Tears of relief. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
Tears of realization. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
He merely wanted to hold me. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
I merely wanted to be held. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
That day, I finally let myself be. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
That day, I finally stopped trying to have my body feel like merely benefit or a burden for others, as if that was its purpose. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This was my body. ⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣
I deserve to be held. ⁣
⁣

🤍
⁣⁣(repost from 2019, back with a new body and a reminder to keep this perspective, because we deserve to be held)
